Women inventors increased their share of international patent applications to 30% in 2016 from 22% in 2002, the World Intellectual Property Organisation said in a report. Female applicants via the Patent Cooperation Treaty system tripled to about 62 400 last year from some 22 600 in 2002. Women in South Korea were closest to gender equality, accounting for 46.9% of patent applications, followed by China with 46.8%.  Biotechnology led the way in gender diversity, with women making up 58% of applications, followed by pharmaceuticals with 56%.    © 2017 Bloomberg